  "body": "I don't have time to hunt for a minimal example that showcases the problem because the behavior comes and goes randomly in a large codebase. Any minimal example might never trigger the issue it seems.\r\n\r\nBut basically I have a function that reverts if 5 minutes has not passed. I use `await time.increase(600)` to get passed 5 minutes. It works 99% of the time, but sometimes it randomly does not. also for some reason calling `console.log((await time.latest()).toString())` sometimes help.\r\n\r\nI'm using `@openzeppelin/test-helpers` for `time`",
